<text>Isn't it amazing when the stars align and you find amazing food made by amazing people?

The vegetarian pies are wicked good. Both the vegetable and spinach feta. It's nice to have an option for meatless that is still a luscious,  tasty entree.

When I'm feeling like having meat, the lamb and rosemary is my favorite.  They work a New-Zealand specific style into it that is phenomenal.

I have interacted with the people behind the pies, and they are warm, lovely people who pour their heart and souls into this family business.<//text>< Gmap_id>

<rate>5< /rate><review>I'm from New Zealand, which IMHO is the home of the best meat pies in the world! I'd heard about Aunty Devi's pie shop years ago (and may even have bought an extra freezer just to accommodate them!) but only got to try them this week, when an errand took me nearby. After being bitterly disappointed by various Australian meat pies in LA (all of which were too dry for my taste) I am glad to report that Aunty Devi's pies are far superior (another example of New Zealand out shining its bigger cousin 😁)! My mince*-n-cheese was the perfect consistency and the pepper steak was tender and delicious! The pastry was perfect too. And Yay! I got 6 for my freezer to take away (not that they'll be in there for very long!). COVID may have stopped me from traveling home to see my family (and eat meat pies to my heart's content) but Aunty Devi's pies fill the pie gap till I can get back to New Zealand. Try them! You'll be glad you did. 😋
*ground beef< /review>< Name>
Tracey Thomas< /Name>

I went to buy parts for the car I was trying to fix and because of an employee  who told me they could test parts before I installed them to determine if they were the problem to my engine I agreed to bring them in. After bringing the parts in I am informed by a younger newer employee who is just learning that they cannot test the parts after another employee informed me they could. Well supposedly a more experienced employee informed they could the following day so I delayed my work in order to find the problem. The following day I take my parts in to be tested and there was no other customer in the store and three employees that appeared to be in a confrontation in front of me the customer who is trying to fix his car. After a good ten minutes or so of just standing there waiting they tell me they can't test the parts.... what the hell is going on here this is not the way to run a buisness. Especially not one where the parts in total run up to 200 300 dollars. This store needs to learn to be more attentive and provide a helpful environment for the customer with adequate knowledge and honest integrity if the employee does not know procedure they should direct the customer to some one that does, and not lie to the customer that they cannot do a service simply because they do not know how to. My experience here was terrible and did not get me closer to fixing my car now I am just stuck with parts that I do not know if they work or not. Spending a lot of money for no reason because this store cannot get their shift together.</text>< pics>

5<//rate>
<Review>Wanted to try a different crepe in this area and choose this one for the cute presentation. Ordered a custom crepe:

Expresso ice cream with chocolate sauce, pudding, custard and whipped cream. Original crepe batter (optional green tea)

Every ingredient was delicious. It had a large amount of whipped cream but it helped balance out the sweetness of the ice cream. The chocolate sauce had small bits of chocolate which greatly helped the texture of the crepe since we ordered all soft ingredients.

There's only 3 tables in the storefront but there are plenty of seats throughout the mall.

Tip: You always need whipped cream. I thank the worker for asking us. CASH ONLY< /Review>< Pics>

< text>
If you have kids, you have to take them here. Bring cash and tip.  Great double rainbow ice cream. Tasty and fresh ingredients.  Cute artistry.  Trying to get not get gluten cereal decor on a cup of ice cream with fruit can be challenging, language barrier. Trying to get crepe free bowl can be challenging.  I need ask what language they speak, so I can learn to ask exactly what I want. I should probably deduct a star, but when I want to suffer with my gluten intolerance, I don't seem to experience enough punishment to dampen the pleasure of these treats.  I prefer their desert crepes.< /text>

< Rate>

< review>
I only came here to pay $8 a crepe because I love novelty food, anything cute, sugar, and well, crepes and ice cream. TBH, I feel like I could stick a couple of colored corn chips and a marshmallow on a scoop of ice cream and call it a bear. Or a dog. Or elephant...

In reality, I wouldn't really buy a whole bag of chips to make one dessert and I sure don't have a crepe stove at home. The verdict - they were actually really good. I like the crepe part which was soft and chewy, and the ice cream (I chose vanilla) was really good too. I tired the green and it tasted natural and not artificial.

Overall, as much as I would like to make fun of this place, it's actually really good and cute as well. I'm such a sucker for cute and sweet foods
-_-< /review>

I've been coming here regularly for over a decade. My main order: green tea boba. I've ordered the crepes before too and am always blown away. <user>110006480612793104456</user>< user_name>
Steven Vong< /user_name>
<date>1430416799991< /date><rating>4</rating>< Text>
Come here if you want to instagram/snapchat/(add other social media) a picture of an adorable animal-shaped ice cream crepe. For a little over $5, you get a crepe with ice cream flavor + sauce of your choice adorned with other toppings to create an overly-cute animal face.

I got a green tea bear with marshmallow snout and fruit loop ears, and paired my ice cream with honey (one of my favorite combos is gt + honey). The crepe was warm, fresh and delicious, and all of the ingredients generally balanced well to make a not overly-sweet dessert. Other toppings such as fruit, having a green tea flavor batter, and sweets will run you a little extra, but they have tons of customization options. My simple crepe was still quite solid, and recommended as a photo-op and snack while taking a break from shopping in Japantown.</Text>

<Rating>4< /Rating>< review>
There's usually a long line everytime I come here but I had to take my sister and her boyfriend here. They loved the kawaii-ness of the crepe but was also surprised that the ice cream itself was good too. They almost did not want to eat it because it was too cute. They had the vanilla and green tea ice cream while I had the strawberry cheesecake one. They're all really creamy and good. The strawberry cheesecake actually had pieces of cheesecake in it. The line relatively goes by quickly and you get your stuff in good time as well. I think it was worth it if you're around Japantown.< /review>

< Text>
So, I was walking actually rushing from the MUNI stop to Fix My Phone SF which to my surprise was only a half block away yesterday evening around 6:00 P.M.  Remind you the establishment closes at 5:00P.M. Another piece of information is the establishment also sells, rents and fixes bikes.  That's the reason I was heading to this location. I work for Postmates and they offer a great deal on leasing a genZe electric bike worth over $3,000 which Fix My phone SF is a distributor for them. Back to the story. When I got to the door it was locked. I knocked not once not twice but three times. No one answered so I thought they were gone for the evening but to what my wondering eyes should appear a gentleman walking a beautiful Maltice and no he wasn't with 8 tiny reindeer, down the sidewalk. When the gentleman approached he mentioned that the store looks as though it was closed. I kind of got the hint that he was the owner. He introduced himself as Michael. He then said "Well I'm kind of going home right now I have a really important date." He let me know that I would have to come back the following day. I explained to him that I just came from San Jose all the way to San Francisco to pick up a bike that I reserved through Postmates. I explained to him also that my transportation was chaotic and I should have been there five hours earlier but was held up because my dog was sick. He then stated "Come on in!" Let me tell you he was so generous and helpful and took his time to explain my lease and the specs on the bike knowing he had to be somewhere else. In fact he received a phone call during our transaction and I could hear the other person on the line requesting his presence. He explained to the person on the other line that he was going to finish helping me and get home as soon as possible. Now let me tell you that is great customer service to have someone go out of their way and stay a half an hour after they closed an hour before hand. I would highly recommend this place for your phone or bike needs and to top it off his prices are competitive to say in the least. What I mean by competitive is low price with quality work.  So the next time you need your phone fixed or you need to purchase a new one or rent a bike for a day stop by Fix My Phone SF located near the corner of Cole & Carl streets in the Haight Ashbury!< /Text>

I recommend this place to anyone who wants to fix their phone, they're worth it. Michael has over 13 years of experience, and knows his stuff. Definitely will be going back if I break anything else.</text>

< Review>
Please note that this review is motivated by my feeling that this business deceived me multiple times and did not bother to offer an appropriate resolution when things went awry. This review has nothing to do with the fact that my phone, ultimately, wasn't fixed. It is unfortunate, because I have no issue supporting smaller businesses like this one.

The story: My iPhone 6 sustained water damage, which required a new screen and battery. I paid for the fix, and realized that the touch ID wasn't working. I took the phone back and paid additional money to get that fixed. A week later, I notice the screen was not properly installed so I went back to get that fixed.

Two weeks later I noticed the battery life was extremely poor when suddenly the phone shut off, and I was unable to restart it. Frustrated, I took the phone back to the store and the technician ran some tests and eventually were able to restart my phone. However, they were unable to discern what the actual issue was - which I found concerning.

Two weeks later, the same issue occurred. This time, the technician told me that my phone was beyond repair and the only "refund" they were willing to offer me was to sell me a used iPhone, and subtract all the fees I had already paid from the price of the phone, which I found incredibly unfair. And they were unwilling to budge, even on a partial refund. They pointed to the store policies, which I believe should only apply when the business does their job.

What's most concerning is that this business accepts cash only, and I now realize why: you cannot dispute this business with your credit card provider. Moreover, their warranty is only 90 days. It's all set up in their favor, and not in the consumer's favor at all. Further, I took my iPhone to two different repair places to run a diagnostic and both stores informed me that the store didn't use genuine parts, and as a result, those parts failed, thus ruining my iPhone.

Again, I'm not mad that my phone wasn't fixed - I'm mad that this business deceived me and were unwilling to operate on fair business practices.<//Review>

So many people here complaining about it...
Anyway, they're there to help you if you help yourself. It's a free program and free job training. You meet people in similar walks of life and its in SD County, where there is a lot more Job Opportunities than other places.
The only reason for the four stars is because other students who don't take the program seriously can ruin it for others. Make friends, but stay away from the idiots.<//text>

<Rate>5</Rate><review>SDJC is AWESOME. I graduated with 2 trades and I was on the honor roll program etc.  If you want to feel sorry for yourself or be in a gang then you will never survive. You have to go with the program and that means RESPECT.Yes the dorms are not the best BUT guess what it is FREE. You also have to realize this was a MILITARY base one time.  You have to earn your privileges  to get off campus except on wknds. And yes they can and will even take that away. Everyone has to wear their badges everywhere they go. You eat when it is meal time and you are told when to go to bed.
I was in the honor roll dorm which was the nicer one and my dorm monitor was cool. We had dances on campus. The pay was not great when I went in 1990, and you even get a clothing allowance and free medical, dental and vision. weekends people went off  campus for the day, went to the beach, mall etc. they have a van that will drop you  off at the trolley. And if really needed $$$ you could go sell Plasma.  we were allowed stereos in our dorms. This is  a GOVT program and they have every right to kick you out if you do not follow the program rules< /review><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Response>None</Response>< gmapID>

< Review>
I am live about 3 ours away from San Diego, originally. I went in 2012, and I loved it! But i ended up getting homesick, and the program i did, was very short. I didn't feel like i would have been equipped for the job. I loved living there because, it's, one, san diego. lol Two, its free and three, I met awesome people. I wish i had stayed for another trade, but I continued my studies in my hometown, and have joined the military. One day I will head back to san diego again. :) It is not a horrible school, you just have to stay away from drama and BS. Stay focused and get what you went there for. Its like a vacation if you aren't from that area lol seriously. I also recommend do everything and anything you can while you are there, because SD never gets boring.</Review>

Dr Yassa does not care about her patients or how her actions affect her patient, their lives and their families. (Look up her public records) Beware.  I came to see Dr Yassa after passing out from low blood pressure, and taking blood pressure medication (ER diagnosis), just to make sure nothing else was going on.  After expressing that I was dissatisfied with the lack of communication on how the tests and timelines were going to work, she dropped me as a patient and left me with a suspended drivers license, which she had reported to the DMV, knowing how hard it is to get in to see doctors right now.  It felt malicious and like the only thing she cared about was her pocket book. Dr Yassa wanted multiple tests, and tried to put me on an anti-seizure medication, “just in case”.  She did not listen to what I had to say, or how I felt. It was her way or the highway. After a brain MRI, EEG and bloodwork, showing no sign of seizures, she still would not sign the paperwork that she had repeatedly assured me that she would sign. Due to liability issues, doctor’s don’t want to sign off on a clean bill of health for the DMV, so I am stuck looking into legal action, and second opinions, trying to find a doctor that will do the right thing and help me get my medical suspension lifted. Don’t trust her, I wish I had never gone to see her.<//review>

< Review>
Seeing everybody's reviews is making me want to post my experience as well, because I wish I would have known before I spent the last 2 years trying to make things work with her. My last visit I left their in tears. This was after they told me to go to Roseville for my apt (I live an hour away), once I got their they stated they didn't have an apt for me and I needed to leave. After countless efforts to try and figure out what went wrong they told me she was actually at her Auburn office that day and could not fit me in. I had to talk to several people before I finally was able to still be seen in auburn that day. During that visit she only spoke to me for a few minutes, which happens EVERY SINGLE TIME I go there. Not including the multiple hour wait in the lobby when I have a scheduled apt. I pretty much had to beg her for my test results which she stated "their fine" and walked out and went on to see the next patient. I was asking her for help on my DMV Paperwork that she is the only one that can sign off on and I have had nothing wrong with me in years to make it to where I shouldn't have my license. She told me she would not do it and she would not let me leave my paperwork there for her office to fill out because I am only a "chart" to her and her office and unless I am right in front of her she will do nothing for me.

I have thought for the longest time that maybe it's just me.. or I just have really bad luck. I am really sad to hear that this happens to so many other people.

Since the first day she met me, my husband was with me and she told me without even saying hello that she would change my meds (that have been making me seizure free) because it is a hard drug to get pregnant on. I tried to talk to her to let her know that that is not what we are looking for in life right now, because she didn't even ask to begin with...

It is so hard to even find the right words to explain how much of a disaster it has been dealing with her and especially her front office as well. Every time I call her office, everyone is extremely rude and treats me as if I am a problem or nuisance to them.

As someone who has epilepsy, doctors like her make you have no hope in ever making your life better. I hope her office can see this and possibly rethink how she runs her practice and treats her patients.... But I am sure nothing will happen because they will do nothing for you unless you are being seen so they can just keep making money off of you.< /Review>

Zero stars does not even come close to how horrible of a person this Dr is. She treated my mother in law so badly & my family. Not to mention every visit or test took FOREVER to authorize because of her disorganized staff.  She showed absolutely no empathy or compassion for what she was going through. She at one point told my family "we are too emotional". My mother in law was falling, losing her ability to speak, dropping her utensils & was progressing rapidly. These are all signs of ALS which anybody can google that! I had a strong gut instinct that she had it. But Dr. Nassa would not listen. She insisted she had MS. She ended up in a wheelchair & told my grandma that we "made her that way" she told us "she can walk" my family left in tears several times. We all wanted answers, some sort of comfort. My mother in law passed away 3 months ago. Dr. Nassa misdiagnosed her with MS, told her she had had it since her 20's, she was going to possibly get better & was having her do extremely expensive infusions for months; which was making her worse. Not to mention signing off on meds for MS (which drs gets paid for when they sign) when we had already switched Neurologists and we let them know several times that she had ALS & will not be going back there. It took her new Neurologist one day to diagnosis her by looking at her MRI & spine test. Dr. Nassa robbed us of our time with her. Made us believe she could get better. We could of done so much more for her if she diagnosed earlier. Instead she passed away 3 months after her diagnosis. I am writing this so this does not happen to anyone else. I hope Dr. Nassa sees this and might decide to be a decent human being & follow the oath she took when becoming a medical doctor!!< /Review>

We placed an order for a chase, sectional, ottoman, and bed with box springs on October 23rd, with an initial estimated delivery for November 22nd. There was an initial delay on the order, with the delivery being pushed back until January. There has since been several more delays in our delivery date, with the most recent estimate being for the 4th of March. We have since cancelled the bed and box springs portion, as we had found a company that had the ability to deliver their order in a timely fashion, and on returning to the store to cancel that portion of the order we were informed that our box springs and bed had been available since December, and that they would in fact be able to deliver that portion, should we have so desired. There has additionally been no attempts at accommodating our long wait. Mors has over-promised and under-delivered, and they are not a company that I am likely to do business with again. <Text>As I write this I am giving Mor 2 stars, hopefully by the end I don't decide to make it a one out of remembered frustration. My wife and I started a full remodel of our 4 bedroom house in the first week of March. Yep, right when the world decided to turn upside down. That story is long and disappointing. Once there was a light at the end of the tunnel in terms of the construction, we decided to start looking for furniture. In mid May my wife and I masked up and went looking for furniture. Jeff at the Moreno Valley location was excellent. We couldn't have been happier with the products we chose. Jeff gave us the time we needed without making us feel pressured or neglected. An absolute superhero of a salesman.

Unfortunately things obviously took a turn for the worst after we gave Mor our money. I don't want to come across as sounding selfish or unsympathetic during these times, but it's now the 27th of July, over 2 months since we handed over thousands of dollars to a company that told us it would initially take up to 5 weeks for delivery. At the time 5 weeks was understandable, the issue is now we still don't have our product. I have been able to speak with only one person on the phone over the past month. My patience is at an all time low with this company. In preparation for writing this review I decided to read some other reviews to see what other people's experiences have been. Well look at that, "bad customer service", "shipment delays", seem to be the top negative comments.

So now is where I have to stop typing. I want to keep the review a two star simply for Jeff. For a company to have no customer service is crazy. It's not like this is something new. If you go back a few years you'll find very similar reviews. I just wish I read them before choosing Mor.</Text>< user_name>

< text>
BEN!!! Go find Ben!!

He’s wonderful and extremely knowledgeable with design!

He’s easy to locate, look for the beautifully dressed man. Lots of people are wearing suits but this guy is always rocking wonderfully trendy attire. That right away led me to believe he’d be a great choice for my home.

I wanted to get someone who had taste, because I lack so much of it! I didn’t want my place to have the “bachelor all pieced together” vibe so I asked Ben a million questions.

He literally walked the facility with me for hours, explaining the color pallets, accent colors,  neutrals... even explained how to breakup rooms with furniture or statement pieces.

I ended up not being in love with a piece at my home so I went back... he was so awesome eye re-walked the floor until I found exactly what I loved.

I’d go back a million times to engage him with questions! Kindest sales interaction I’ve ever had and also one of the best human stranger interactions I’ve ever had.

Please go find this man so he can give your home a makeover and also your style of you need it!!< /text>

<text>Great purchase! Quality furniture at a fair price!
We went to a few furniture stores in the area looking for a genuine leather sectional. Saw this one as soon as we walked in and loved it.
Kirk ended up giving us a tour of the store but we already made up our mind. Best part is it was on sale for $800 off and no sales tax!
Kids stayed entertained with cookies, popcorn and soft drinks.
Process was smooth and great.
On the way out from ordering the sectional we found a table we liked and ordered that as well. As someone who builds custom furniture for a living i was surprised to see a table and 4 chair set for less than $300 and it fit the style of our home. I was reluctant to purchase a table when I build them everyday for people but for $300 I couldn’t pass up that deal, and it gives me more free time with the kids and wife!

Bought a L sectional sofa about 2 months ago. The couch started to wear out and break very fast, we tried out the floor model couch it was very firm which is what we looking for because we have back pain, but the couch we received was a not firm like the one we tried on. Then the arms rest frame break shortly after 2 months of normal use. Mor customer service said it was our fault to cause the damage by putting our hand on the armrest when getting up, therefore they can only do repair not replace ! Over the phone they told me it will take 3 days to repair at shop. In reality, the couch where they repaired the frame was returned to me after a month ! Then the 3 cushions will be delivered to me on 12/30/18, which is like 2 months from my repair request date !
Overall, i am disappointed with the quality of the couch, if you are considering any couch there especially like the one i bought, beware the quality is very bad.  The repair inspector told me manufacturer put "cardboard" under the round armrest that fail.

< Review>
The first night I went there I told the salesman the items I wanted to purchase. He told me that it was almost 9 and that they were close to closing and asked if he could call me the next day about the items I wanted. I was blown away that a furniture store would kick someone out that was there to spend about $2,000 on furniture. I've worked on commission my entire life. If any of my employees kicked out a customer because it was close to closing time I'd have them leave and tell the customer to stay. You NEVER let someone with AmEx in hand walk out the door.

The part that is even worse is that he called me back,  told me the piece I wanted was in San Diego. I could pay for it over the phone and have it delivered to my house the next day or delivered to the store to pick it up in about a week. I told him I don't like using my credit cards over the phone or internet so I'd just go there in person to pay for it after work. He was not working that night so he asked me to see a partner of his which I'm assuming would help him so he didn't lose his commission. I find that ironic because he wasn't too worried about his commission the night before when he kicked me out of the store.

I showed to and asked for the person he told me to ask for. He wasn't there. The girl that helped me said she's partners with the guy I was supposed to see and that she'd help me. I guess they're splitting the commission 3 ways now?

She goes to write up my order and tells me that the part that was supposed to be delivered to my house the next day or picked up at the store in a week is actually on back order and has an e.t.a. of 36 days?  Pathetic! Needless to say that after being lied to and kicked out of the store that this will be the last time I do business with them.<//Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
I'd like to start by saying first impressions are everything. My first impression of this store was "WARNING! SALES PERSON!" That was thanks to an unsavory fellow by the name of Thomas. Typical, young and inexperienced sales guy trying to make his suggestions without gathering my reson for walking or motives. Straight "sharp angle" me into a "full set discount" that I clearly voiced I had no need for but to quote him verbatim "it will look ugly and be a childish decision to go with just a couch, add a lamp table to make an adult decision". So I was immediately thinking I'm walking around for five minutes then walking out . As I'm doing my five minute courtesy walk out I met Lorena B. She was asking questions that had nothing to do with sales just casual small talk, although I'm aware this is a sales strategy she seemed genuine and that's all that was necessary for me to stay. Long story short Lorena helped me make a purchase based on what I wanted and what she recommended. Not once did I feel pushed or forced to buy , it took about five hours for me to make up my mind. I can say that if all I had seen at this store was Thomas I would of walked out and gone straight to the next one. But Lorena and even Jason (the manager) made it a very carefree and comfortable environment earning my business. At the end of the day I will be back and so will my friends and family just for Lorena. Thank you.

PS. Mentirosa!!<//review>

<user>100906698620629867318<//user><pictures>None<//pictures><date>1377751496622</date><review>I wanted to share my great experience I had with this place. I needed a bed and mattress for my guestroom since my mother was going to be staying with me for about a month. I looked them up online and decided to go in. I was greeted by a young lady named Malia and I told her what my needs were. She showed me around a little and was extremely helpful, then let me browse on my own. I ended up walking into their mattress area and was in awe at how mattresses have changed in the last few years. Anyway, a guy named Buller (that's what he goes by, but his first name is Luis) came in and started showing me a few models. He laid me down on a TempurPedic just to try it out. I told him I wasn't shopping for myself but rather a guest room. I ended up in that mattress gallery for over an hour with him haha. Well let me just tell you, I ended up waking out of the store with not only the bedroom set  and mattress for my guest room, but an amazing TempurPedic Cloud Supreme for myself, a new couch, and a TV Stand.  I did their financing which to me was a shock on how long they offer interest free financing for (seemed like forever).  My payment was like $88 for everything! The delivery of the bedroom and mattresses was super fast, next day. The couch and TV stand took 3 weeks to order.  This is probably one of the biggest purchases I have ever made apart from my house and auto, but Luis and Malia were amazing! I never felt pressured or ignored, being in sales myself, that's not easy to accomplish with a guest. Greats service, great staff, the values are awesome, and great financing! They have free soft drinks, popcorn, and cookies for kids too :) If you want a great mattress go see them!
